# Design Tokens

Source of truth: `design-tokens/` directory. W3C Design Tokens v2025.10 format.

## Token File Structure

- `base.tokens.json` — color primitives (OKLCH)
- `breakpoints.tokens.json` — responsive breakpoints
- `components.tokens.json` — component-specific tokens
- `data-viz.tokens.json` — chart/visualization colors
- `elevation.tokens.json` — shadow/depth tokens
- `glass.tokens.json` — glassmorphism tokens
- `motion.tokens.json` — duration, easing, springs
- `opacity.tokens.json` — opacity scale
- `typography.tokens.json` — font sizes, weights, line heights

## Rules

- All tokens use `$value` and `$type` (W3C format). Add `$description` for non-obvious tokens.
- Token names map to `--sc-*` CSS custom properties after build.
- After editing any `.tokens.json` file, run `cd design-tokens && npm run build` to regenerate outputs.
- Generated outputs: CSS (`_tokens.css`), Kotlin (`DesignTokens.kt`), Swift (`DesignTokens.swift`), C (`design_tokens.h`).
- Never hand-edit generated output files — edit the `.tokens.json` source.
- Reference `docs/design-strategy.md` for the design philosophy behind token choices.
